race.comment: HIT THE JACKPOT (7) is a distance specialist who finished out of the money two starts back then was 6.5L off them in Saturday grade last time out. Has been kept up to the mark with a recent trial and drops plenty of weight today with the claim of Cheung. Can sit up on the speed from an inside draw and give them something to catch. ONEMORETWOMANY (6) missed the placings when resuming two runs back then didn't feature last start when 7L away last time out. He was good in this grade two back. Can bounce back to his best.. ZING TO WIN (2) built on a nice third two starts back at Kalgoorlie with a win over 1100m, getting home by 0.8 lengths. Nicely placed to go back-to-back. PRINCE RAGNAR (4) has been in the placings in his past two starts, finishing third over 1203m at this track last time out. Has a high cruising speed. Can feature in the finish. SURE NO SOMETHING (5) can be on the speed from a good draw and won't be far away.
